content:
Check:
  all:
    - name: SETCD
      operator: non_empty
    - name: SETCD
      operator: is_not_contained_by
      value: $tx_setcd
Operations:
  - domain: TX
    id: $tx_setcd
    name: SETCD
    operator: distinct
Core:
  Id: CDISC.SENDIG.113
  Version: '1'
  Status: Draft
Description: The value of SETCD in DM must be one of the SETCD values in TX.
Outcome:
  Message: SETCD is not present in TX.SETCD
Rule Type: Record Data
Sensitivity: Record
Authorities:
  - Organization: CDISC
    Standards:
      - Name: SENDIG
        Version: '3.1'
        References:
          - Origin: SDTM and SENDIG Conformance Rules
            Rule Identifier:
              Id: '113'
              Version: '1'
            Version: '2.0'
            Citations:
              - Cited Guidance: Subject (animal) may belong to one and only one Trial
                  Set.
                Document: IG v3.1
                Item: Specification
                Section: 5.1.1.1
Scope:
  Classes:
    Include:
      - SPECIAL-PURPOSE
  Domains:
    Include:
      - DM

json.Description: The value of SETCD in DM must be one of the SETCD values in TX.

Outcome.Message: SETCD is not present in TX.SETCD

Citations.Cited_Guidance: Subject (animal) may belong to one and only one Trial Set.
